I mean they've gone out of their way to try and constantly innovate the way the space operates. ERC721A having the most insanely low gas prices during an 5000 NFT sell out at 0.25 ETH in seconds flat. completely insanity, this is only the beginning huge thanks to the team !ttp

there are tons of genuine people who believe in what they do and having a bunch of people that can support their vision and assist them along the way in building something truly great is what has separated Invisble Friends from most other NFT communities i've been a part of 6/?

about the entire NFT space before joining. I used to be a massive discord grinder trying to get every WL possible so that I could minmax profits and I just can't really bring myself to do it anymore after how I've seen a real community can be built from the ground up. 5/?

it was simply about community first. the amount of art and value that's been created by that community would not have been the same if they'd done this any other way. the people I've met through being an Invisible Friends member have really grounded me in terms of what I thought

they didn't even start running giveaways on twitter before they'd built up a grass routes group of loyal community leads that would be able to set an example to the new people joining, there was no grinding, there was no interaction farming, there was no backdoor connections 3/?

I've listened to every twitter space they've ran and kept up with every update. It's still so crazy to me that most people aren't aware of the bar they're trying to set as a leading web3 brand, the community was never fostered in an inorganic (like 40k members with no plugs) 2/?

from being a part of the IF Community since mid november and interacting with the dev team/community daily I'm so happy to see that all of the work they've put in is finally being recognized. even with all of the exponential growth that's happened in this short time period 1/?
